Article and Author Management System
This Python program provides classes for managing articles and authors for a magazine publication system. It allows users to create articles, authors, and magazines, and perform various operations such as retrieving articles by author, listing magazines, adding articles to magazines, and more.

Features
Article Class: Represents an article with attributes such as author, magazine, and title.
Author Class: Represents an author with attributes like name and methods to manage articles.
Magazine Class: Represents a magazine with attributes including name, category, and methods to manage articles and contributors.
Functionality: The system provides functionalities like adding articles, retrieving articles by author, listing magazines, listing article titles, listing contributing authors for a magazine, etc.
Usage
Setting Up:
Ensure you have Python installed on your system.
Download the article_management.py file.
Running the Program:
Import the classes into your Python script or interactive environment.
Create instances of the Author, Magazine, and Article classes to manage articles, authors, and magazines.
python
Copy code
from article_management import Author, Magazine, Article

# Example Usage
# Create an author
author1 = Author("John Doe")

# Create a magazine
magazine1 = Magazine("Tech Magazine", "Technology")

# Add an article
article1 = Article(author1, magazine1, "Python Programming")

# Retrieve articles by author
author1_articles = author1.articles()

# List magazines
magazines = author1.magazines()

# Add more functionality as needed...
